    "This observation should at least make one suspicious of the formulation, and has motivated a host of proposed alternatives, such as defining the risk taking into account only the downside [Mar59, Chap.",
    "This criticism is also valid, on the surface.",
    "But when the parameters are chosen appropriately, and the data are reasonable, portfolios constructed from mean-variance optimization do not suffer from this alleged deficiency.",
    "We should maximize expected utility.",
    "A more academic version of the previous criticism is that portfolios should be constructed by maximizing the expected value of a concave increasing utility function of the portfolio return [VNM47]."
